Steven Gerrard has urged Raheem Sterling to reach an agreement with Liverpool over a new contract.

The forward, who scored twice in the 3-1 victory over Bournemouth in the Capital One Cup quarter-final on Wednesday, has turned down a £70,000 a week offer.

Liverpool chief Brendan Rodgers claims Sterling, 20, is one of the biggest talents in Europe and compared him with Arsenal forward Alexis Sanchez after his performance against Eddie Howe’s team.

