Gerrard, who is weighing up an extension to his own deal at Liverpool, said: ‘I hope he signs a new contract at the club because I think this club is perfect for him, certainly for the next few years.

‘He’s going to play most weeks, the fans love him here. He can progress here and become a top, top player so I hope the people around him give him the right advice because he should stay.

‘Raheem’s got potential to be top drawer for sure. He took a lot of stick after the weekend but I thought his all-round performance was magnificent, the only thing that was missing was a finish.

‘The exciting thing for all of us is that he’s English and going to be a top, top player.

‘He’s great to watch, great to play with, he’s got that pace. When you look up he’s always giving you an option and that’s what I’ve thrived on throughout my career at Liverpool with the likes of (Fernando) Torres, (Michael) Owen.

